### 2. Reduced-form VAR(1)

We estimate a VAR(1) on data from 1985M2 to 2019M12 (418 observations). We stop before 2020 to avoid the COVID-19 period biasing the estimates. The variable ordering is: EPU, PAYEMS growth, INDPRO growth, PCEPI growth.

#### 2d. Estimated equations

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{epu}_t \;=\;& 46.067 + 0.641\;\text{epu}_{t-1} - 19.313\;\text{payems\_g}_{t-1}\\
                  & - 3.540\;\text{indpro\_g}_{t-1} - 13.225\;\text{pcepi\_g}_{t-1} + u_{\text{epu},t}
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{payems\_g}_t \;=\;& 0.058 - 0.000278\;\text{epu}_{t-1} + 0.679\;\text{payems\_g}_{t-1}\\
                        & + 0.017\;\text{indpro\_g}_{t-1} + 0.033\;\text{pcepi\_g}_{t-1} + u_{\text{payems},t}
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{indpro\_g}_t \;=\;& 0.111 - 0.0014\;\text{epu}_{t-1} + 0.925\;\text{payems\_g}_{t-1}\\
                        & + 0.073\;\text{indpro\_g}_{t-1} + 0.458\;\text{pcepi\_g}_{t-1} + u_{\text{indpro},t}
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{pcepi\_g}_t \;=\;& 0.168 - 0.0006\;\text{epu}_{t-1} + 0.021\;\text{payems\_g}_{t-1}\\
                       & + 0.009\;\text{indpro\_g}_{t-1} + 0.404\;\text{pcepi\_g}_{t-1} + u_{\text{pcepi},t}
\end{aligned}$$

#### 2e. Covariance matrix of residuals

|           | epu      | payems\_g | indpro\_g | pcepi\_g |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-----------|----------|
| epu       | 964.407  | -0.182    | -0.946    | -0.098   |
| payems\_g | -0.182   | 0.011     | 0.019     | 0.001    |
| indpro\_g | -0.946   | 0.019     | 0.317     | -0.002   |
| pcepi\_g  | -0.098   | 0.001     | -0.002    | 0.028    |

